1
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,160
You ungrateful son.

2
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,360
You're more shameless than I ever thought.

3
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:51,480
I hate you.

4
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:53,760
<i>You fought with your dad again?</i>

5
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,360
<i>This time is probably the last time.</i>

6
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,680
<i>He set me free.</i>

7
00:02:57,760 --> 00:03:00,960
Matching cases? What does he want?

8
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,440
Why are you this stupid, huh?

9
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:06,400
<i>And my head hurts, not my legs.</i>
<i>Why are you holding me like this?</i>

10
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:08,400
Can't I take care of you for once?

11
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,560
The other day, you kicked me out.

12
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,200
<i>Today, you're happy I'm back?</i>

13
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:15,000
How can someone change overnight, Dad?

14
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,840
Mr. Trai!

15
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,600
You think I sent someone to kill you?

16
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,680
It makes perfect sense.

17
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:29,000
So where would someone
smart like you keep the evidence, then?

18
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,720
Why aren't you resting?

19
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,280
Why did you come outside?
It's cold out here.

20
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,560
Trai.

21
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,800
Dad.

22
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,880
Have you ever missed Mom?

23
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,440
Why do you suddenly mention her?

24
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,560
It's nothing.

25
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,120
I've just wondered for a long time,

26
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,720
but I never dared to ask.

27
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,320
On the night Mom died,

28
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,880
why didn't you come see her?

29
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:53,440
Do you know how scared I was?

30
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:55,960
I didn't know what to do.

31
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,800
I called you, but you didn't answer.

32
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,280
Mom was seriously ill. You knew that.

33
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,240
How could you let her pass away like that?

34
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,760
How could you leave me alone with Mom?

35
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,800
I had no money.

36
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,280
I had to make money.

37
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,920
Money?

38
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,320
Money again, Dad?

39
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:20,920
Yes.

40
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:25,520
Only money
could have saved your mother's life.

41
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,680
She had cancer,

42
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,080
and it was terminal.

43
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,000
It needed a huge amount of money,
and I didn't have it.

44
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:38,840
I had no money, so I couldn't save her.

45
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,520
Even if I had stayed by her side that day,

46
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,920
I still couldn't have helped her.

47
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,600
Do you know how painful it is

48
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,480
to stay beside the person you love

49
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,000
but be completely powerless?

50
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,640
Isn't it better not to stay at all?

51
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,800
Do you think I didn't suffer?

52
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,320
I wanted to be a good husband to Duangdao.

53
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,360
I wanted to be a good father to you.

54
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:17,880
But all of those things have a price.

55
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,320
They can only be bought with money.

56
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,880
I realized it
on the day your mother passed away

57
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,120
that we must have money.

58
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:33,840
Because one day, when you're sick,
I'm sick, or the people we love are sick,

59
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,560
only money will save us.

60
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,440
Only wealth…

61
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,800
will allow us to live well.

62
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,160
But you're already rich now.

63
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,400
So why did I almost die anyway?

64
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,080
I'm not arguing

65
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:11,560
that if you'd had money back then,
Mom might have lived longer.

66
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,120
But I don't agree with you thinking
it's some kind of miracle cure.

67
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,240
Money can create many things,

68
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:22,080
but it can destroy many things too.

69
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:25,920
You and I barely
feel like a family anymore,

70
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,360
isn't that because of money?

71
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,360
I'D LIKE TO CANCEL THE EVENT NEXT MONTH

72
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,440
I'D LIKE TO CANCEL

73
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,600
I'D LIKE TO POSTPONE OUR DEAL

74
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,720
MR. PETCH, I NEED TO CANCEL OUR DEAL
PLEASE UNDERSTAND ME

75
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,680
I'D LIKE TO CANCEL OUR DEAL

76
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,560
All the clients canceled?

77
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,840
I'm sorry for lying.

78
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,480
I just didn't want you to worry.

79
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,200
It's over…

80
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,880
- It's…
- Petch.

81
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,480
- Sit down first.
- Sit down.

82
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,720
Slowly. Be careful.

83
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,280
Petch.

84
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,280
Calm down.

85
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:19,200
Petch, you once said you wanted me
to be your business partner, right?

86
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,440
From today on, I'll be your partner.

87
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:26,000
I'll stress with you,
solve problems with you.

88
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,960
Whatever you face, I'll face it too.

89
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,440
We'll fight together.

90
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:41,120
I saved this money to invest,
and I want to invest with you.

91
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,160
This is my partner registration fee.

92
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,880
TRANSACTION COMPLETE
100,000 BAHT

93
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,920
100,000?
Where did you get this much money?

94
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,960
From my beauty and cuteness, obviously.

95
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,800
Totally legal.

96
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:07,160
It should be enough to help us
get through this period

97
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,440
until we find new jobs.

98
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,280
I may not be able to help with money,

99
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,720
but I'm ready to fight for you anytime.

100
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,560
Me too.

101
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:20,240
Even if I'm not as tough
as Samlee or Pakbung,

102
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,480
I'm good at praying.

103
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:25,120
I already made a vow,
asked for money, asked for jobs.

104
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,760
I'm even giving up meat for three months.

105
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:35,560
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you, everyone.

106
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,560
Hello?

107
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,440
Yes, this is Petch.

108
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:55,760
Yes, I can go now.

109
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,240
What is it?

110
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,520
A client asked to meet about a job.

111
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,840
Wow.

112
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:09,400
Then we have to celebrate.
Celebrate. Celebrate.

113
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,000
- Stop.
- Celebrate. Huh?

114
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,040
You vowed to stop eating meat
for three months.

115
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,600
Oh, right.

116
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,680
Then let's go vegetarian.

117
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,480
I'm so happy. So happy.

118
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,120
I don't wanna go vegetarian…

119
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:37,280
Application promo booth?
There are more than ten events.

120
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,840
Do they all have to follow
the same design?

121
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,080
You can follow
what's written in the document.

122
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,400
He looks weird.

123
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:53,800
Could he be a scammy?

124
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,480
What scammy?

125
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,160
Scammer!

126
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,280
What's the app about?

127
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:06,000
Uh… it's an app about…

128
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,320
Finance.

129
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:11,800
Job guidance.

130
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,280
No, it's finance, idiot.

131
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,840
Oh. No, it's finance, idiot.

132
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:24,400
That's our specialty.
We're good at this kind of work.

133
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:28,160
If you're interested,
you can sign right there,

134
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,080
on the last page.

135
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,480
Oh?

136
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:36,720
Why does it already list my company

137
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,240
and your name too?

138
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,760
Excuse me.

139
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,280
Who recommended you to us?

140
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,160
Pong!

141
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:49,600
Uh…

142
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:50,560
Mr. Pong.

143
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:52,760
Pong?

144
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,280
I don't know any Pong.

145
00:11:57,880 --> 00:12:00,480
I'm not familiar with that name either.

146
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,400
Or

147
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:06,280
could it be your man?

148
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,160
Mr. Rachen?

149
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:13,560
I told you not to play here, boys.

150
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:16,040
I'm so sorry. I'm really sorry.

151
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,400
Apologize to the uncles.

152
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:21,400
- I'm sorry.
- I'm really sorry.

153
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,040
Wrap it up and leave.

154
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,280
Yes.

155
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:29,680
If you're interested, please sign there.

156
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,920
I have to go somewhere else.

157
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:38,160
- They called us uncles?
- It's because you look old.

158
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,440
Mr. Trai.

159
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:53,120
So you brought
your dad's company's job to us?

160
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,960
Well.

161
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:57,040
I had to find an event organizer anyway.

162
00:12:57,120 --> 00:13:01,240
I just took Petch's portfolio
and presented it to the team, that's all.

163
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:05,080
We proposed it in the meeting,
following proper procedure.

164
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,920
No pulling strings.

165
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,120
Meh.

166
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,000
What do you mean, "Meh"?

167
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,320
I thought you'd use your connections
to help a friend.

168
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:16,880
Why would I help someone
who spends all day livestreaming

169
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:18,760
and wouldn't even come visit me?

170
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:24,080
Well, who do you think

171
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,400
saved your life?

172
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:29,360
Mr. Trai actually meant to repay you.

173
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:31,920
That team meeting
was basically just Mr. Trai himself…

174
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,480
But Mrs. Mook

175
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:41,400
is also a shareholder of Be Rich,
isn't she?

176
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:43,520
- Won't this cause problems?
- No.

177
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,240
Even if it does, I'll handle it.

178
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:48,440
You should focus
on doing a great job for me.

179
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,320
Okay.

180
00:13:58,360 --> 00:14:02,040
Guys, want to go order drinks?
Let's order some drinks.

181
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:05,000
Come on. Let's go.

182
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:15,760
So you finally decided
to throw money at someone.

183
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,320
What money did I throw at you?

184
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,560
What I gave you was work.

185
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:23,880
I had Prarop draft the contract

186
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,280
and put your name in it too.

187
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:27,960
When you work, you'll earn money.

188
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:30,280
And when you have money,
you can buy a new phone.

189
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,280
Oh, so your principle is to give work

190
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,440
but not money.

191
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:41,520
Work equals value.
Money destroys friendships.

192
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,960
But without money,

193
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:47,440
you couldn't give me
this job in the first place.

194
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,280
What? What are you muttering about?

195
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:00,680
Thank you.

196
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:04,120
Thank you for helping me and Petch.

197
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,000
Your wound's healed already, right?

198
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,320
And if it's not healed yet?

199
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,160
What are you selling me this time?

200
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:20,960
There's one thing that heals everything.

201
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:31,080
BBQ. I'll treat you.

202
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:38,520
Wow.

203
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,080
This meal

204
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,960
is on me.

205
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:44,760
Thank you, Mr. Trai,

206
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,440
my knight in shining armor.

207
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:49,720
- Knight?
- Knight?

208
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:54,840
And thanks to the three beautiful girls

209
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:57,040
for taking such good care of me.

210
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,000
Thank you so much.

211
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,440
Of course.

212
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:03,280
And for this meal,

213
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:05,160
don't go home until you're full.

214
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,240
- All right then.
- Dig in.

215
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:11,760
Here.

216
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:13,320
Didn't you say BBQ?

217
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:16,560
I forgot.

218
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,960
Niuniu made a vow not to eat meat.

219
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,160
Oh.

220
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,760
Did I make it? Did I make it?

221
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:25,760
Hello, hello.

222
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:26,680
You made it.

223
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:27,600
Come, sit here.

224
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,720
Wow.

225
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,080
It's good.

226
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,240
Dig in.

227
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,280
Yummy.

228
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,040
What, you're not eating?

229
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,520
I'm not used to food like this.

230
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:46,160
I'm afraid of getting diarrhea.

231
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:52,160
Oh, please, delicate stomachs.

232
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:54,120
If you're not gonna eat, gimme.

233
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,880
- Hey, we're eating it over here.
- We're eating.

234
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:09,880
Aren't you eating, Mr. Trai?

235
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,079
Petch.

236
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:23,200
I'll just take the kindness, thanks.

237
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:26,160
As for the food, I…

238
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,840
Don't spit it out yet. Chew first.

239
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,800
Chew.

240
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:41,040
- Wait, what is this?
- Grilled intestine.

241
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,520
Grilled intestine?

242
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:45,000
Hey, this is actually really good.

243
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,040
Yeah.

244
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:49,760
Then try this.

245
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:55,520
Papaya salad with fermented fish.

246
00:17:58,080 --> 00:17:59,200
Delicious.

247
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,880
- Whoa.
- Yeah.

248
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:03,080
Well,

249
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,640
if you're going this far, I'm in too.

250
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,720
Excuse me.

251
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:11,560
Spicy shrimp salad
with lots of fermented fish chunks.

252
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:14,800
Spicy pork bone soup. And a
jungle papaya salad, lots of fish chunks,

253
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:15,800
extra chili.

254
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:17,560
It's okay, right?

255
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,080
Yes.

256
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,840
I'm eating too.

257
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:26,960
Didn't you say

258
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,440
- you weren't used to it?
- Yeah.

259
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,080
I am now.

260
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:34,880
What about you over there?

261
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,280
Weren't you scared of diarrhea?

262
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:38,480
Well, someone has to accompany
Mr. Trai to the bathroom.

263
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,920
- Whoa.
- Wow.

264
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,840
You're all talking.

265
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,440
What?

266
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:51,520
So it really is actual intestines? Really?

267
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,640
Hey, don't take mine.

268
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,840
- You did it again.
- Here it comes.

269
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:57,000
- What? What is it?
- Fermented fish? Over there.

270
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:58,280
Fermented fish. Whose is it?

271
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:00,320
It's mine. Thank you.

272
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,800
Hey, put it down.

273
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,480
Calm down.

274
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,760
Don't steal mine.

275
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:08,040
- Delicious.
- Delicious.

276
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,960
Right?

277
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,720
Wow.

278
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,000
What else do I need to eat?

279
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,400
Five custards,

280
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:20,720
five sweet fillings,
two quail eggs, and one sausage.

281
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:23,440
Okay, one moment.

282
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,200
- Make it ten each.
- Sure.

283
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:32,760
- Why are you buying so much?
- There are a lot of people.

284
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:36,040
What filling did you order? Sweet, right?

285
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:37,080
Extra cream, please.

286
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:39,280
Sure. One moment, please.

287
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,200
Oh?

288
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,560
- What?
- You pay.

289
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,600
Didn't you say you'd treat?

290
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:53,960
I'll scan to pay.

291
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,760
Right there.

292
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:01,960
You bought a new phone?

293
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,760
Then can I see your phone?

294
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,920
Rachen bought this for you?

295
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,800
And you took it?

296
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,320
Hey, wait, Mr. Trai.

297
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,400
I know you don't get along
with Mr. Rachen,

298
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,160
but can't you separate hating him

299
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:46,600
from something I need to use?

300
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:49,080
I need a phone to make a living.

301
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,760
Can't you see it?

302
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,160
Rachen is trying to buy you.

303
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,200
And don't you know

304
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:03,400
that one phone can't buy me?

305
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,200
Then what if Rachen spoils you even harder

306
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:10,600
and gives you everything you want?

307
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,320
Would you still stay by my side?

308
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:17,000
Why aren't you answering?

309
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,320
I'm thinking.

310
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,600
Hey!

311
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:28,160
Hey!

312
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:30,080
- Hey!
- Someone got hit by a car!

313
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:31,120
Hey.

314
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,640
What?

315
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:38,880
Does anyone know CPR?

316
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,400
Me! Me! Please move aside.

317
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,160
You stink of booze!

318
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,680
- I'm not drunk.
- Uncle, you're drunk!

319
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:46,600
- You're drunk.
- I'm not.

320
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:47,680
You're drunk.

321
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:55,480
Hey.

322
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:58,000
Are you alright?

323
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,040
Mr. Trai.

324
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,400
Mr. Trai, are you okay?

325
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,480
Mr. Trai, let's go back.

326
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,520
This way.

327
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,200
- Hey.
- It's alright.

328
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:12,160
I'll take care of him.

329
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:44,000
Trai, I'm scared.

330
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,880
I hit someone. He's dead.
I'm scared, Trai!

331
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,520
I'm scared, Trai!

332
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,960
What do I do?

333
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,040
Don't be scared, Da.

334
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:55,920
I'll take responsibility.

335
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:58,040
I'll tell the police

336
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,160
I was the one driving.

337
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:02,280
Alright?

338
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:03,800
Trai…

339
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:05,600
Mr. Trai.

340
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,120
Please calm down.

341
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,640
Don't say anything yet. Let me handle it.

342
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:23,080
Trai.

343
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:35,520
Tomorrow, come with me.

344
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:37,560
Where?

345
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,040
Come on, Da.

346
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:14,640
Where are you taking me?

347
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,160
Hello.

348
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:36,440
Hello.

349
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,640
Are you Wasan's mother?

350
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,120
Yes.

351
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:43,120
Are you his friend?
I've never seen you before.

352
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:45,640
May I come inside?

353
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:53,880
Sure.

354
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,120
Why are you bringing me here?

355
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:02,280
Trai.

356
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:03,200
Come on, Da.

357
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,240
- Please, come in.
- No.

358
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:06,400
- Trai.
- Come on.

359
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:08,920
Is his dad home?

360
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,840
Why are you here?

361
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,360
Dear.

362
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:20,240
He's San's friend.

363
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:21,600
No.

364
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:24,400
Someone told me he's the one
who drove into our son.

365
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:28,000
He's some rich kid. He paid someone
to go to prison for him.

366
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,120
I'm sorry.

367
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,280
The news said a woman was driving…

368
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:41,840
Was it true?

369
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:43,840
No.

370
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:47,200
It wasn't me. I had nothing
to do with it. I don't know anything!

371
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,640
Trai, why did you bring me here?
I wasn't involved.

372
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:50,600
It was because of me.

373
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:53,160
I had a part in your son's death.

374
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:55,640
I'm truly sorry.

375
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,520
What are you sorry for now?

376
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:01,760
It's been three years.

377
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:08,480
I'm sorry.

378
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:09,920
Will your apology

379
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:12,120
bring my son back?

380
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:15,960
My son was about to graduate.
He was going to be a doctor,

381
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:18,000
to save who knows how many people!

382
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:20,400
But because you
and your friend were drunk,

383
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,840
my son had to die!

384
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,960
You killed my son!

385
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,160
You!

386
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:28,000
I wasn't involved!

387
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:30,000
- I wasn't involved!
- Dear.

388
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:34,280
- Because of you!
- That's enough.

389
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:37,880
Don't come here apologizing
just to make yourself feel better.

390
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:41,400
You ran from your crime for years.
Why dig it up again?

391
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:46,040
Do you know
how hard it was for us to move on?

392
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:49,760
- Go! Get out!
- I'm sorry.

393
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:51,880
We won't forgive you.

394
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,600
We don't want your apology.

395
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:56,200
- Get out!
- Get out!

396
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:59,640
- Get out now!
- Get out!

397
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,880
Get out!

398
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:03,520
Dear.

399
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,360
Dear.

400
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,320
Dear, where are you going?!

401
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,320
Stop.

402
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,880
You killed my son.

403
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,000
No!

404
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:58,200
Dear! Stop!

405
00:27:58,280 --> 00:27:59,560
What the hell are you doing?!

406
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,400
You want to become a murderer
because of him?!

407
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:05,760
I'm sorry. I miss our son.

408
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:14,640
Calm down.

409
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,760
Calm down.

410
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:37,880
I didn't do it. It wasn't me.

411
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:39,520
I wasn't involved.

412
00:28:40,040 --> 00:28:41,720
It was Trai.

413
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:45,000
He forced me to drink. I wasn't involved.

414
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:47,080
No…

415
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:51,920
I wasn't involved. I didn't do it.

416
00:28:54,840 --> 00:28:56,120
It was Trai…

417
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:59,680
I didn't do it.
I'm sorry. I wasn't involved.

418
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:15,240
Is Mr. Trai okay?

419
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:35,520
Mr. Trai?

420
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:43,280
In the past,

421
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,200
I liked getting my dad's attention.

422
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:49,080
I acted out,

423
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:53,040
stayed out late,
didn't care about anything.

424
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:55,920
And that day, I drank.

425
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:58,360
So I made Darin drink too.

426
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:01,840
And we…

427
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,720
we hit someone. He died.

428
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,960
Even last night, I still dreamed about it.

429
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:20,440
The image of him covered in blood

430
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:23,120
still haunts me.

431
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:26,800
I had to see a psychiatrist.

432
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:32,840
He was about to graduate from med school.

433
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:35,840
He had a good future.

434
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:38,720
He was going to save so many people.

435
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:44,160
And look at me.

436
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:47,840
It took me three years

437
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,960
just to go apologize to his family.

438
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:53,280
I'm such a coward.

439
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:57,760
It makes sense they'll never forgive me.

440
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:04,400
You should carve this mistake
into your heart

441
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:08,160
and use it to fix your future.

442
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:14,280
Fix my future?

443
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:16,920
Yes.

444
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:20,280
You have to live
to make amends for what you did.

445
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:22,440
Let the person who died

446
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,840
push you forward.

447
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:27,760
He was a doctor, right?

448
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:32,240
Look, you're building a school.

449
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:34,680
Then you have to make new doctors.

450
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,600
Make ten, twenty great doctors

451
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:39,520
to replace what was lost.

452
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:42,000
It won't erase what you did,

453
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:45,120
but at least, it'll give you purpose.

454
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:49,080
You'll find meaning in staying alive.

455
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,560
Are you some kind of life coach?

456
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,360
Wait a sec.

457
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,360
Stars shine in the dark.

458
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:22,040
So you have to be brave like a star,

459
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,480
like your mom.

460
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:30,280
You have to complete your star mission.

461
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:32,960
Your courage and your mom

462
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,920
will stay with you, always.

463
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:45,560
Don't give up, Mr. Trai.

464
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:00,160
Then what about you?

465
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:03,760
Will you stay by my side?

466
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:19,000
My life isn't terrible enough already?

467
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:23,960
Why would he drag me to those people?!

468
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:27,880
Why is everyone so cruel to me? Why?

469
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:29,640
Why?!

470
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,560
Do you feel better?

471
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:42,360
If I don't,

472
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,680
what are you going
to report to Mr. Rachen?

473
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,880
It's not your fault.

474
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,120
I know you're the victim.

475
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:56,200
Why…

476
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,520
You went out with Trai?

477
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,159
Yes.

478
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,880
Where did you go?

479
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,520
Can you just stay out of it?

480
00:35:00,080 --> 00:35:03,240
I don't care where you go or what you do.

481
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:06,520
Just don't do anything
that brings shame to my dad.

482
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:08,560
Don't forget who you are now.

483
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:15,280
I'd like to know that too.

484
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:20,000
Who am I, exactly?

485
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:26,200
Darin!

486
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,400
Are you crazy?

487
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,080
I used to be with Trai,

488
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:35,200
but then I had no choice.

489
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:37,640
I had to become your dad's wife.

490
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,600
So what am I, exactly?

491
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:51,880
How about being your woman too?

492
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,200
- Darin!
- How about that?

493
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,960
Wait, Darin. Calm down.

494
00:35:58,040 --> 00:36:00,040
Wait. What's wrong with you?!

495
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:01,080
Get a grip!

496
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:03,280
And who made me like this?

497
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,760
You people!
I ended up like this because of you!

498
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:08,280
Hey! Try blaming yourself for once, Darin.

499
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,480
- Think before you act.
- Mr. Rachen.

500
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:11,840
Mr. Rachen.

501
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,640
Mr. Trai and Ms. Darin
didn't go anywhere improper.

502
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:19,760
Mr. Trai took her to the doctor's house,
the one from the car crash.

503
00:36:22,640 --> 00:36:24,800
All of you trample on me,

504
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,080
you hurt me.

505
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:31,520
But I'm shameless.

506
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:35,200
I won't run. If I run, I lose.

507
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:38,000
I'll stay and make you all suffer

508
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:40,720
until the day you collapse.

509
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:45,320
It won't be long
until you will all be ruined!

510
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:57,920
Trai. Trai.

511
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,520
You little bastard.

512
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:02,600
Wake up.

513
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:06,280
Wake up now. We need to talk.

514
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:12,440
Huh?

515
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:18,240
It's over. I handled it.

516
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:21,200
Everyone's taken care of.
Why dig it up again?

517
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:22,920
You want to go to jail?

518
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:32,880
You told Dad?

519
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:37,080
I didn't tell them

520
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:39,760
you hired someone to take the fall for me.

521
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:42,160
I'm still a coward. Okay?

522
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:45,120
So smart when it comes to stupid things.

523
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:54,520
I knew it.

524
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:58,360
People don't change overnight.
It's impossible.

525
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:00,640
Don't change the subject.

526
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:03,800
And that slum kid you're hanging out with,
don't think I don't know.

527
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:10,880
A 10-million-baht contract

528
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,120
for them to improve the Be Rich app?

529
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:14,080
Are you insane?

530
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:17,280
10 million for that girl.

531
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,280
What is this?

532
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:22,720
Dad owns the company.
He should know everything.

533
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:27,960
She does this for a living.

534
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:30,600
Her company has a portfolio.
It's credible.

535
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:32,880
You never learn.

536
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:37,680
That girl is using you to get ahead,
just like Darin.

537
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:41,840
You have zero instincts.
People always trick you,

538
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:44,000
scam you. They take advantage of you.

539
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,680
You want me to work with you, right?

540
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:56,040
Here. This is my starting point.

541
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:58,640
Be Rich isn't just Dad's.

542
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:03,760
I'm the second-largest shareholder,
so I own Be Rich too.

543
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:08,160
Consider this my request.

544
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:10,120
No.

545
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:15,520
If you want authority, then go work.

546
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:20,040
Go sit at a desk
and work like an owner does.

547
00:39:20,120 --> 00:39:22,000
- Can you do that?
- Sure.

548
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:24,200
Today then?

549
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:29,840
You want me to work, right? I'll show you.

550
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:37,280
Get ready to serve Be Rich's
second-generation owner,

551
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,960
Mr. Board Member.

552
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,240
Good morning.

553
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:54,200
Hey. There.

554
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:59,600
Ignore them. Not our problem.

555
00:41:03,080 --> 00:41:06,560
Keep an eye on him.
I really don't trust him.

556
00:41:06,640 --> 00:41:08,000
Yes, Dad.

557
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:08,880
This way, Mr. Trai.

558
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,120
SCAM COMPANY

559
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:22,600
This month's new campaign
is the Be Rich cash card.

560
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:25,360
We're partnering with famous global brands

561
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:28,800
in clothing, shoes, bags, cosmetics.

562
00:41:28,880 --> 00:41:31,880
Anyone who wants to own these luxury items

563
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:33,840
can borrow them through us.

564
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:35,840
Zero percent interest for three months.

565
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,960
Sorry, there are
so many moths flying around.

566
00:41:44,320 --> 00:41:47,680
A campaign that looks all shiny
and beautiful is like a bonfire.

567
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:50,640
It just lures moths in to die.

568
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:55,960
- Trai.
- You must have

569
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:58,000
a different idea.

570
00:41:58,520 --> 00:41:59,720
Would you like to present something?

571
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:13,680
How about "The More You Borrow,
the Richer You Get" campaign?

572
00:42:15,120 --> 00:42:18,800
Let them borrow to buy equipment for work
but also teach them how to save money.

573
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:20,120
How's that? Good?

574
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:27,280
A lending business
that wants people to learn how to save?

575
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:30,120
That's uniquely unconventional.

576
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:33,520
This is the son
you wanted working here, Mr. Tritot?

577
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:38,240
I have to apologize
on behalf of my brother.

578
00:42:39,520 --> 00:42:42,240
He's new. He may have
misunderstood some things.

579
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:45,600
Misunderstood what?

580
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:49,760
A luxury brand campaign,
zero interest for the first three months.

581
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:53,800
Then next month, it jumps to 30 percent,
then steps up 10 percent like a staircase

582
00:42:53,880 --> 00:42:55,920
because we want customers
to be unable to pay interest,

583
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:58,760
so we can seize their house,
their car, their land and sell it off.

584
00:42:58,840 --> 00:43:00,080
Then what?

585
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:03,000
Thank you, everyone. Meeting adjourned.

586
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:06,200
Last year, Be Rich ran a campaign
for people to borrow funds to buy crypto

587
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:07,600
and invest in overseas stocks,

588
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:11,320
targeting laborers
who had zero financial knowledge.

589
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,240
And what happened?

590
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:17,280
3,432 people lost their assets,

591
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:20,040
and 1,758 are currently suing.

592
00:43:20,120 --> 00:43:21,720
Is everything I just said

593
00:43:22,920 --> 00:43:23,920
correct?

594
00:43:28,680 --> 00:43:30,800
If you think you studied this so well,

595
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:32,480
then you should understand

596
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:34,960
every investment has risk.

597
00:43:35,040 --> 00:43:38,320
And we clearly warn them every time.

598
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:44,200
But we didn't give them information.
We didn't even choose partners for them.

599
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:47,680
Do you think we're running a charity?

600
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:50,560
If they want to invest,
they have to study for themselves.

601
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:52,480
How can we spoon-feed everything?

602
00:43:52,560 --> 00:43:55,920
Trai, we didn't force anyone,
and we didn't break the law.

603
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:58,080
We're just giving them what they want.

604
00:43:59,560 --> 00:44:02,240
So they got rotten crypto
and worthless stocks.

605
00:44:03,120 --> 00:44:05,280
And how did it end? They lost everything.

606
00:44:13,640 --> 00:44:15,000
A lending business

607
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:17,520
works with people's desires.

608
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:20,080
How can we be responsible
for all of their greed?

609
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:28,040
We push people to spend money
then blame them for being greedy.

610
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:32,440
We give them zero knowledge
then call them stupid.

611
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:37,720
A business that looks down on customers
doesn't love them, doesn't help them grow,

612
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:42,120
will never ever prosper, I think.

613
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:47,080
Are you insulting my mom?

614
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:48,440
Mika.

615
00:44:53,120 --> 00:44:54,400
Trai.

616
00:44:59,400 --> 00:45:00,480
Trai!

617
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:02,320
You little bastard.

618
00:45:03,240 --> 00:45:04,640
So you came here to embarrass me?

619
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:07,200
I'm just showing my vision.

620
00:45:07,280 --> 00:45:11,000
Vision, my ass. It goes
against the company's principles.

621
00:45:12,040 --> 00:45:15,920
The more you borrow, the richer you get?
Idiot. That's how we go bankrupt.

622
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:19,520
You wanted to show everyone
that you're against me, didn't you?

623
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:21,440
You wanted to expose me

624
00:45:21,960 --> 00:45:23,760
and show everyone
I was terrible at raising my kid.

625
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:27,040
Dad.

626
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:29,400
Do you see that?

627
00:45:31,360 --> 00:45:33,400
Earlier, there were only
a dozen of people. Now there are more.

628
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:37,800
Those are the people who got crushed.

629
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:39,160
We seized their assets.

630
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:40,960
So what?

631
00:45:41,880 --> 00:45:43,960
Even if more people come,
what can they do to us?

632
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:46,760
Don't look down
on the people with nothing left, Dad.

633
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:49,520
You got threatened, and I almost died.

634
00:45:50,280 --> 00:45:51,440
This could be the reason.

635
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:55,800
You used to have nothing too.
You've been in their places.

636
00:45:57,280 --> 00:45:59,640
Have you forgotten
how hard it was back then?

637
00:46:01,680 --> 00:46:02,960
Don't change the subject.

638
00:46:04,120 --> 00:46:06,480
If you came to stir up trouble,
go back home.

639
00:46:10,800 --> 00:46:13,280
You're the one kicking me out.
I always listen to you.

640
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:17,480
But I think…

641
00:46:21,640 --> 00:46:23,360
real rich people

642
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:27,400
don't build their lives
on other people's suffering.

643
00:46:32,680 --> 00:46:33,560
Go wherever you want.

644
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:54,120
He's on the same side
as that rotten Pakbung.

645
00:46:54,720 --> 00:46:58,840
He insulted you too, Mom. I hate him.
I hate him, hate him, hate him.

646
00:47:00,520 --> 00:47:01,480
Mika.

647
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:06,120
It’s clear to every executive right now
that Trai is being defiant.

648
00:47:06,200 --> 00:47:07,760
He's not fit to work here.

649
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:10,160
So why are you upset?

650
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:13,600
This is good for us. You should be happy.

651
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:16,800
But he defied you.

652
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:19,920
He crossed the line.
Aren't you going to teach him a lesson?

653
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:21,160
Mika.

654
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:27,400
An enemy who's stupid?
We don't need to do anything.

655
00:47:28,760 --> 00:47:30,400
He'll destroy himself.

656
00:47:34,200 --> 00:47:36,240
You just stay still

657
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:39,920
and don't act stupid like you did earlier.
Understand?

658
00:48:03,560 --> 00:48:07,200
No. I'm not in the mood to work now.
I'm leaving with Mom.

659
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:13,160
On second thought,
please take me home, Rachen.

660
00:48:13,240 --> 00:48:15,080
And stop by my friend's hotel too.

661
00:48:15,160 --> 00:48:16,840
I want to eat at the chef's table there.

662
00:48:19,960 --> 00:48:23,360
Good thing I dodged in time.
Otherwise, I'd get slapped by Ms. Mika.

663
00:48:24,520 --> 00:48:25,640
Uh, Ms. Mika.

664
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:28,240
You were going
to the restroom, weren't you?

665
00:48:31,320 --> 00:48:32,480
Restroom, miss.

666
00:48:33,400 --> 00:48:34,920
Have you seen the clip
that a good Samaritan posted yet?

667
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:37,280
Too bad it was kinda far away though.

668
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:41,280
But if we find a better clip,
the faces might be clearer.

669
00:48:42,240 --> 00:48:43,400
Was that your doing?

670
00:48:46,120 --> 00:48:48,320
Uh, Ms. Mika.

671
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:50,840
Have you ever heard the saying

672
00:48:51,360 --> 00:48:54,920
"What is done by night appears by day"?

673
00:48:56,320 --> 00:48:58,840
For people who do wrong
because their hearts are rotten,

674
00:48:58,920 --> 00:49:00,840
no matter how much dirt
they bury it under,

675
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:04,480
the stench still rises.

676
00:49:04,560 --> 00:49:06,000
A stench like…

677
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:14,760
- You!
- Ms. Mika, please don't.

678
00:49:14,840 --> 00:49:15,760
Stay out of this!

679
00:49:16,280 --> 00:49:18,480
- Ms. Mika, please don't.
- I said stay out of this!

680
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:24,000
You're the one who stinks like shit.
You filthy runt,

681
00:49:24,080 --> 00:49:26,440
hanging around the poor so much
that you start to smell like them.

682
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:28,240
And you still have the nerve to insult me?

683
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:31,160
Just because you're Uncle Tritot's son,

684
00:49:31,240 --> 00:49:33,560
you think I won't dare touch you?

685
00:49:34,160 --> 00:49:36,520
Listen, your dad and you

686
00:49:36,600 --> 00:49:38,320
are just new money.

687
00:49:38,400 --> 00:49:39,960
You think you can compete with my family?

688
00:49:40,560 --> 00:49:43,200
My mom is friends
with politicians from every party.

689
00:49:43,280 --> 00:49:45,320
Generals, lieutenant generals,
everyone's her friend.

690
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:49,280
Trash like you can't win against my mom.

691
00:49:49,360 --> 00:49:52,520
But you assaulted my friend.
You have to take legal responsibility.

692
00:49:53,160 --> 00:49:56,240
Even if I killed your friend,
I still wouldn't be guilty of anything

693
00:49:57,080 --> 00:49:58,200
because I'm rich.

694
00:49:58,840 --> 00:50:01,000
And my mom is even richer. Remember that.

695
00:50:01,080 --> 00:50:02,080
Hey!

696
00:50:05,600 --> 00:50:07,400
You just admitted it yourself.

697
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:08,960
What was that?

698
00:50:16,840 --> 00:50:18,200
What do you mean?

699
00:50:19,720 --> 00:50:20,760
Why are you smiling?

700
00:50:23,120 --> 00:50:23,960
Alright.

701
00:50:29,000 --> 00:50:30,080
Mika.

702
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:39,320
You two sort it out yourselves.
I'm out. I'm scared.

703
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:41,280
- Hey!
- Mika.

704
00:50:42,360 --> 00:50:43,440
Please.

705
00:51:16,920 --> 00:51:19,480
I didn't start it. But that…

706
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:22,720
Your brother is the one who started it.

707
00:51:24,280 --> 00:51:27,160
I understand. That's just how Trai is.

708
00:51:32,120 --> 00:51:33,080
I'll take you home.

709
00:51:44,960 --> 00:51:45,800
After you.

710
00:51:59,880 --> 00:52:02,000
<i>Real rich people</i>

711
00:52:02,920 --> 00:52:05,880
<i>don't build their lives</i>
<i>on other people's suffering.</i>

712
00:52:09,520 --> 00:52:11,480
Who taught you to think like that?

713
00:52:16,880 --> 00:52:17,880
Prarop,

714
00:52:19,200 --> 00:52:20,480
handle something for me.

715
00:52:26,480 --> 00:52:27,560
Pakbung,

716
00:52:28,080 --> 00:52:31,160
if it's hot, take a break.
You're gonna get heatstroke.

717
00:52:31,240 --> 00:52:34,800
I'm okay, Petch.
I've been sipping water the whole time.

718
00:52:37,280 --> 00:52:38,600
Honestly,

719
00:52:39,560 --> 00:52:43,280
my friends didn't really mean
to throw a birthday party.

720
00:52:44,080 --> 00:52:45,320
They probably feel sorry for me,

721
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:49,240
so they're doing this so they can hire me.

722
00:52:49,960 --> 00:52:52,440
Petch, stop.

723
00:52:53,160 --> 00:52:54,560
Don't think like that.

724
00:52:55,080 --> 00:52:57,200
What we need to focus on

725
00:52:57,280 --> 00:52:59,560
is how to make this event turn out great,

726
00:52:59,640 --> 00:53:02,480
so your friends are happy
and want to throw parties every holiday.

727
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:07,360
And most importantly,
they'll hire us for every single one.

728
00:53:10,760 --> 00:53:13,920
This is an opportunity, Petch.
Don't see it as a crisis.

729
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:23,920
So dirty.

730
00:53:26,440 --> 00:53:27,720
Pakbung.

731
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:30,240
Yes?

732
00:53:44,600 --> 00:53:45,920
Have a seat.

733
00:54:01,680 --> 00:54:02,520
Your face.

734
00:54:13,520 --> 00:54:15,560
PHOTO

735
00:54:21,480 --> 00:54:22,480
Thank you.

736
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,400
I don't want you to be friends with Trai.

737
00:54:35,400 --> 00:54:37,160
That's so straight to the point.

738
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:41,280
I didn't even get to eat anything.

739
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:42,880
Stop seeing Trai.

740
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:46,440
- How much do you want?
- Stop seeing him?

741
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:50,120
Stop being friends.

742
00:54:50,760 --> 00:54:53,160
Stop getting involved.
Stop contacting him.

743
00:54:53,240 --> 00:54:55,360
Act like you never knew him.

744
00:54:55,880 --> 00:54:57,760
Fade out of each other's lives
if possible.

745
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:00,640
How much do you want, Pakbung?

746
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:06,280
Did Pakbung go to see my dad?

747
00:55:06,920 --> 00:55:08,000
Yes.

748
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:14,240
She went with the other guy,
the one that's not Lee.

749
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:19,000
Was it Prarop?

750
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:22,600
Yes. Prarop. Mr. Prarop took Pakbung.

751
00:55:37,960 --> 00:55:38,800
So?

752
00:55:40,120 --> 00:55:41,480
How much do you want?

753
00:55:42,720 --> 00:55:45,240
Can I have some time to think?

754
00:55:46,320 --> 00:55:47,280
Why do you need to think?

755
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:50,960
You're not going
to stop seeing my son, are you?

756
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:55,240
I just need to calculate first

757
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:58,280
whether you're paying by check or cash,

758
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:02,120
the full amount upfront
or by installments,

759
00:56:02,640 --> 00:56:04,240
and whether there'd be
any withholding tax.

760
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:07,000
What are the terms?

761
00:56:08,320 --> 00:56:10,440
Do I need to move houses
to avoid Mr. Trai too?

762
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:14,320
So I can add that to the price.

763
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:16,400
Are you trying to mess with me?

764
00:56:17,400 --> 00:56:18,440
No.

765
00:56:19,040 --> 00:56:20,320
I'm excited.

766
00:56:21,520 --> 00:56:23,520
I'm so happy.

767
00:56:23,600 --> 00:56:28,880
I've wanted to meet someone who
throws money at me for a long time.

768
00:56:36,920 --> 00:56:39,320
Then you should stop him. She's my friend.

769
00:56:39,840 --> 00:56:41,840
How could you let my dad
threaten my friend?

770
00:56:41,920 --> 00:56:44,840
Mr. Tritot isn't threatening her.
He's just asking her to name a price.

771
00:56:44,920 --> 00:56:45,840
Yeah, whatever.

772
00:56:45,920 --> 00:56:48,520
You're just gonna let my dad
buy my friend? Go in and stop him.

773
00:56:49,240 --> 00:56:52,000
Mr. Trai, you don't trust your own friend?

774
00:56:53,360 --> 00:56:55,560
<i>You think Pakbung</i>
<i>can be bought too, don't you?</i>

775
00:57:03,040 --> 00:57:04,560
I'll take three.

776
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:07,840
Playing coy, huh?

777
00:57:10,280 --> 00:57:11,120
300,000?

778
00:57:11,720 --> 00:57:13,880
300,000 can't even buy a car.

779
00:57:14,600 --> 00:57:15,800
Then you want 3 million?

780
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:18,160
Or 30 million?

781
00:57:22,640 --> 00:57:25,920
<i>Mr. Tritot, how much do you think</i>

782
00:57:26,640 --> 00:57:28,600
<i>your son is worth?</i>

783
00:57:29,680 --> 00:57:30,840
PRAROP

784
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:39,240
<i>The thing between us</i>
<i>will never end with me.</i>

785
00:57:39,320 --> 00:57:40,480
<i>It's you.</i>

786
00:57:41,080 --> 00:57:42,720
<i>If I were just a little higher up,</i>

787
00:57:43,320 --> 00:57:44,600
<i>I wouldn't have to envy Trai.</i>

788
00:57:45,480 --> 00:57:48,640
You signed a contract without
consulting the board. If we can't deliver,

789
00:57:48,720 --> 00:57:50,160
this is going to blow up.

790
00:57:50,240 --> 00:57:52,280
Then make it work.
What's so hard about that?

791
00:57:52,360 --> 00:57:54,880
Why? Can't you work with your brother?

792
00:57:54,960 --> 00:57:57,480
Or do you want to be
the company chairman instead of me?

793
00:57:57,560 --> 00:58:00,360
Trai is making my plan
a lot harder to execute.

794
00:58:00,440 --> 00:58:01,840
- Go!
- Please stop!

795
00:58:01,920 --> 00:58:02,840
Go!

796
00:58:02,920 --> 00:58:04,560
- Come out!
- You're dead!

797
00:58:04,640 --> 00:58:06,680
- Don't come closer!
- Dad!

798
00:58:06,760 --> 00:58:08,120
I'm sorry.

799
00:58:08,200 --> 00:58:10,640
I'm sorry I couldn't be a good father

800
00:58:10,720 --> 00:58:12,280
sooner.

801
00:58:12,880 --> 00:58:14,200
<i>For our family,</i>

802
00:58:14,920 --> 00:58:16,680
<i>I'll try one more time.</i>

803
00:58:16,760 --> 00:58:19,800
You're still going to let
your brother run Be Rich?

804
00:58:19,880 --> 00:58:22,800
Then all that's left
is the chairman's seat.

